output: For each test case, print a line containing an integer equal to the remainder of Fib ( Fib ( N ) ) divided by M.
input: The input consists of several test cases and ends with EOF. Each test case consists of a line with two integers N and M (1 ≤ N ≤ 109, 2 ≤ M ≤ 106).
name: Fibonacci Again!
description:
The famous Fibonacci sequence can be defined as follows:


	Fib( 1 ) = Fib( 2 ) = 1
	Fib( N ) = Fib( N-1 ) + Fib( N-2 ), for N > 2


Your task is simple, calculate the value of the remainder of Fib ( Fib ( N ) ) divided by M.
